  "prompt": "Which is the best app to make anonymous call online?",
  "response": "There are several apps and services that allow users to make anonymous calls online. Here are some popular options:\n\n1. **Burner**: This app provides temporary phone numbers that you can use to make calls and send texts anonymously.\n\n2. **Hushed**: Similar to Burner, Hushed gives users the ability to create temporary phone numbers for anonymous calls and texts.\n\n3. **TextNow**: While primarily a messaging app, TextNow allows users to make calls using a secondary number.\n\n4. **Google Voice**: You can create a Google Voice number to make calls, which can help keep your primary number private.\n\n5. **Sideline**: This app offers a second number for personal or business use, allowing for calls to be made without revealing your actual number.\n\n6. **Cloak**: This app specializes in making anonymous calls and allows you to disguise your caller ID.\n\nKeep in mind that while these apps can help maintain your anonymity, individual use cases, features, and privacy policies can vary, so it's always a good idea to read user reviews and terms of service before choosing one. Additionally, respect local laws and regulations regarding anonymity and privacy when using these services.",
